title: Early Turnout Appears to Be Highest in 23 Years
description: As Israelis go to the ballot box for the fifth time in less than five years, voter fatigue has been a prominent concern. But an early figure provided by the country’s public broadcaster suggested that the electorate was still engaged.
dc:creator: The New York Times
media:credit: Avishag Shaar-Yashuv for The New York Times
media:description: Voting during Israel’s parliamentary election at a polling station in Bnei Brak, Israel, on Tuesday.
